		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Sat Jul 31, 2010 6:02 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In 8x16 pixel mode:
<br />
<br />OAM tile number $14 -&gt; $0140 and $0150
<br />OAM tile number $15 -&gt; $1140 and $1150
<br />OAM tile number $16 -&gt; $0160 and $0170
<br />OAM tile number $17 -&gt; $1160 and $1170
<br />
<br />It's convenient that the base of the hexadecimal number system commonly used for VRAM addresses is the same as the length of one tile in bytes.
<br />
<br />Lode Runner has an "edit mode" with 8x16 pixel sprites and no scrolling. It was the first 8x16 game I ever encountered.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


